The paper deals with medical image segmentation using deep learning techniques, which falls under the computer vision (cs.CV) category. The use of weak supervision and attention-based convolutional neural networks suggests a focus on machine learning (cs.LG) and artificial intelligence (cs.AI) subcategories. The use of CT scans and PACS systems suggests a focus on multimedia (cs.MM) and information retrieval (cs.IR) subcategories.
